3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the design of MIMO cellular networks, which are a type of social network, where users are connected to each other through base stations. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of linear beamforming and interference alignment techniques for improving the performance of MIMO cellular networks, which are commonly used for multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes an unstructured approach to linear interference alignment, which involves designing transmit beamformers to satisfy conditions for IA without explicitly identifying the underlying structures for IA.
